  "description": "This goose shaped bird was found among a flock of primarily Canada (lesser) and Cackling geese (Richardson). When standing the bird was about the same size as neighboring Cackling geese. Black face, bill, neck, and upper breast. Thin white neck collar extending from sides of the neck across the front of the neck. Mantle, Upper, and Lower Scapulars gray. White flanks with some barring near the rear of the flanks. White vent and lower tail coverts with black on the tail.",
